## Root Cause Analysis

The build fails because it tries to use `/usr/bin/python3.11` which doesn't exist in this openSUSE Tumbleweed environment (only Python 3.13 is available). The spec file is iterating through Python flavors including `python311`, but that interpreter isn't installed.

## Solution

Use `%pyproject_wheel` and `%pyproject_install` macros, which automatically detect available Python versions. Ensure the spec has proper BuildRequires for python-rpm-macros:

```
BuildRequires:  %{python_module pip}
BuildRequires:  %{python_module wheel}
BuildRequires:  python-rpm-macros
```

The `%pyproject_wheel` macro will automatically use only Python versions available in the build environment (3.13 in this case), skipping unavailable versions like 3.11. This eliminates the "No such file or directory" error for missing interpreters.